e Saturday Evening Post:

January 21

Sir,

There are many excellent things in Mr. Gold's article, but it is most unfair of him to have quoted a converesation he and I had about a common friend. That friend was, and is (for he is still very much alive—and very much upset) no other than Sam Fortuni, the poet. Sam tells me that he has seen Mr. Gold only once, forty years ago, and would have never dreamed of asking him for a loan. I may add that—in refutation of the statements attributed to me